name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.datanode.max.slowdisks.to.exclude
description:
The number of slow disks that needs to be excluded. By default, this parameter is set to 0,
    which disables excluding slow disk when choosing volume.

name: dfs.client.write.exclude.nodes.cache.expiry.interval.millis
description:
The maximum period to keep a DN in the excluded nodes list
  at a client. After this period, in milliseconds, the previously excluded node(s) will
  be removed automatically from the cache and will be considered good for block allocations
  again. Useful to lower or raise in situations where you keep a file open for very long
  periods (such as a Write-Ahead-Log (WAL) file) to make the writer tolerant to cluster maintenance
  restarts. Defaults to 10 minutes.

name: dfs.datanode.data.transfer.bandwidthPerSec
description:
Specifies the maximum amount of bandwidth that the data transfering can utilize for transfering block when
      BlockConstructionStage is
      PIPELINE_SETUP_CREATE and clientName is empty.
      When the bandwidth value is zero, there is no limit.

name: dfs.block.access.key.update.interval
description: Interval in minutes at which namenode updates its access keys.

name: mapreduce.job.end-notification.retry.attempts
description:
The number of times the submitter of the job wants to retry job
    end notification if it fails. This is capped by
    mapreduce.job.end-notification.max.attempts

name: dfs.mover.movedWinWidth
description:
The minimum time interval, in milliseconds, that a block can be
    moved to another location again.

name: httpfs.buffer.size
description: The size buffer to be used when creating or opening httpfs filesystem IO stream.
